        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:59PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over White Oak, or 10 miles northwest of Elizabethtown,
moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ruskin, Bladen Community College, Duart, Ammon, White Oak, Jerome,
Dublin, and Tar Heel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
